97
00:04:30,859 --> 00:04:31,943
Shut up, Glenn.

98
00:04:38,783 --> 00:04:39,784
I think you look great.

99
00:04:39,868 --> 00:04:42,954
Professional, serious,
a proper team leader.

100
00:04:43,038 --> 00:04:46,416
Does make me feel authoritative,
like that chick from Law and Order.

101
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:52,130
"Well, boys, looks like
we've got ourselves an SVU."

102
00:04:53,340 --> 00:04:54,466
I've never seen the show.

103
00:04:54,549 --> 00:04:56,801
Okay. Who we got next?

104
00:04:59,679 --> 00:05:02,015
Linda? Come on in.

105
00:05:02,098 --> 00:05:07,145
So, you, Linda Johannsen,
are in the Good Place.

106
00:05:08,146 --> 00:05:09,147
That's nice.

107
00:05:10,565 --> 00:05:13,943
I know this can be a little overwhelming,
but you'll get used to it.

108
00:05:15,070 --> 00:05:16,237
Do you have any questions?

109
00:05:17,155 --> 00:05:18,531
Is there a fitness center?

110
00:05:18,615 --> 00:05:19,991
There can be,

111
00:05:20,075 --> 00:05:24,746
plus literally anything else
you could possibly wish for.

112
00:05:24,829 --> 00:05:28,958
Just in case we weren't clear,
this is the Good Place.

113
00:05:29,042 --> 00:05:30,794
A state of eternal happiness.

114
00:05:31,961 --> 00:05:33,171
Paradise.

115
00:05:33,963 --> 00:05:35,215
That's nice.

116
00:05:36,299 --> 00:05:37,634
I like that.

117
00:05:39,969 --> 00:05:42,514
So, the Bad Place sent Simone
to mess with Chidi,

118
00:05:42,597 --> 00:05:43,681
John to mess with Tahani...

119
00:05:43,765 --> 00:05:45,975
Do you think they sent Linda
to mess with Jason?

120
00:05:46,059 --> 00:05:49,437
She's from Norway.
Is Norway, like, the opposite of Florida?

121
00:05:49,521 --> 00:05:51,064
All I know is she's boring.

122
00:05:51,147 --> 00:05:54,359
She makes Neutral Janet
look like Disco Janet.

123
00:05:55,193 --> 00:05:57,654
Disco Janet was around
for a while years ago.

124
00:05:57,737 --> 00:05:59,072
She was great.

125
00:05:59,155 --> 00:06:01,658
I mean, she was a lot, but she was fun.

126
00:06:01,741 --> 00:06:05,036
Actually, that's a good idea.
Let's unload this dead weight.

127
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,496
- Janet?
- Hi, there!

128
00:06:06,579 --> 00:06:08,123
Linda, this is Janet.

129
00:06:08,206 --> 00:06:11,584
If you want anything at all,
Janet can bring it to you. Watch.

130
00:06:11,668 --> 00:06:16,047
Janet, can I have a baby elephant
made of pure light

131
00:06:16,131 --> 00:06:18,758
that tells you true secrets
about the universe?

132
00:06:19,425 --> 00:06:22,303
- Shirley Temple killed JFK.
- See?

133
00:06:22,387 --> 00:06:23,638
Anything you want from Janet?

134
00:06:24,806 --> 00:06:27,851
Can I have... a peppermint?

135
00:06:27,934 --> 00:06:29,102
Sure!

136
00:06:32,063 --> 00:06:33,648
I'm going to go over there now.

137
00:06:36,818 --> 00:06:38,945
Stonehenge was a sex thing.

138
00:06:45,451 --> 00:06:47,370
Brent, come on in.

139
00:06:48,496 --> 00:06:52,208
So, you, Brent Norwalk, are dead.

140
00:06:53,209 --> 00:06:54,961
Really? Well, that blows.

141
00:06:55,044 --> 00:06:56,754
Uh, you know what?
Maybe it's a good thing, actually.

142
00:06:56,838 --> 00:06:58,131
Some journalist was poking around,

143
00:06:58,214 --> 00:06:59,924
calling all these ladies
who used to work for me.

144
00:07:00,008 --> 00:07:01,467
You can't even make a joke these days.

145
00:07:01,551 --> 00:07:02,594
Everything is so PC.

146
00:07:02,677 --> 00:07:05,138
And I was an equal opportunity
offender, okay?

147
00:07:05,221 --> 00:07:06,222
I made jokes about everybody.

148
00:07:06,306 --> 00:07:08,975
And, by the way,
I'm the furthest thing from racist.

149
00:07:09,058 --> 00:07:10,852
My dentist was a black woman.

150
00:07:11,352 --> 00:07:13,062
I just think people need to loosen up.

151
00:07:13,146 --> 00:07:14,731
So, where am I exactly?

152
00:07:16,316 --> 00:07:17,525
The Good Place.

153
00:07:18,276 --> 00:07:20,195
Cool. Good.

154
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:25,158
So, Brent, I see from your file
you were in the materials business.

155
00:07:25,241 --> 00:07:26,618
Oh, yeah. Big time.

156
00:07:26,701 --> 00:07:30,371
Strings, cords,
vinyl, synthetics, rubber...

157
00:07:30,455 --> 00:07:31,873
We do vulcanized now, so that's huge.

158
00:07:32,582 --> 00:07:35,293
Plus metals. Aluminum, brass, copper.
What else?

159
00:07:35,376 --> 00:07:37,587
- Steel?
- No, not steel.

160
00:07:37,670 --> 00:07:38,796
Steel's a sucker's game.

161
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:40,507
Polymers, coatings, internals...

162
00:07:40,590 --> 00:07:44,010
You crack open an HVAC, that is all us.

163
00:07:44,093 --> 00:07:45,720
Is there golf here?
There freakin' better be.

164
00:07:45,803 --> 00:07:49,807
Okay, well, why don't you
explore around a bit while I go far away?

165
00:07:49,891 --> 00:07:52,644
And if you need anything,
you can always ask Janet.

166
00:07:52,727 --> 00:07:54,521
- Janet?
- Hi, there! How can I help you?

167
00:07:54,604 --> 00:07:56,397
A secretary. Great.

168
00:07:56,481 --> 00:07:59,817
- Not a secretary.
- Fine. Executive assistant.

169
00:07:59,901 --> 00:08:02,195
Here we go with all the "terms"
we got to learn, right?

170
00:08:02,278 --> 00:08:06,199
Vice President of Helping! Captain Marvel!
You know what I'm saying.

171
00:08:06,783 --> 00:08:07,867
I'm not part of this.

172
00:08:07,951 --> 00:08:08,952
Let me show you around.

173
00:08:10,954 --> 00:08:12,997
Well, Linda must be here for Jason,

174
00:08:13,081 --> 00:08:16,751
because Brent is definitely here
to annoy the fork out of me.

175
00:08:17,335 --> 00:08:19,837
Everyone, you may remember
Matt from Accounting.

176
00:08:19,921 --> 00:08:22,340
The Judge has assigned him to our project.

177
00:08:22,423 --> 00:08:24,300
So, I'll be monitoring
the four new humans.

178
00:08:24,384 --> 00:08:27,804
A modified points system will be applied
to their actions for the next year,

179
00:08:27,887 --> 00:08:29,514
and then we'll know
how much better or worse

180
00:08:29,597 --> 00:08:31,474
their behavior is
than when they were alive.

181
00:08:31,558 --> 00:08:34,143
But no one will be able to see
what's happening in real time.

182
00:08:34,227 --> 00:08:35,937
Good luck saving humanity
from eternal doom!

183
00:08:42,151 --> 00:08:43,695
Okay, forget about
all that stuff.

184
00:08:43,778 --> 00:08:46,239
For this first week, all we need to do

185
00:08:46,322 --> 00:08:49,033
is figure out what the fork is up
with these benches.

186
00:08:49,117 --> 00:08:51,202
So, I made this.

187
00:08:51,786 --> 00:08:55,915
We start them out on this side,
because we're like, "What's your deal?"

188
00:08:55,999 --> 00:08:58,751
And when we feel we have a handle
on who they are,

189
00:08:58,835 --> 00:09:01,421
what makes them tick,
we move them to this side...

190
00:09:02,297 --> 00:09:03,172
Party time!

191
00:09:03,256 --> 00:09:05,967
We already know a lot about Simone, so...

192
00:09:07,093 --> 00:09:07,927
Boom!

193
00:09:08,011 --> 00:09:09,887
See? One down, three to go.

194
00:09:09,971 --> 00:09:11,306
Let's go figure out the others.

195
00:09:11,389 --> 00:09:12,557
We can do this.

196
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:15,393
On three. "Dead eyes, eat hearts,
can't lose!"

197
00:09:16,603 --> 00:09:19,897
Sorry, old Bad Place rallying cry.

198
00:09:19,981 --> 00:09:22,400
Aww!

199
00:09:22,483 --> 00:09:24,986
Janet, he's walking around again.

200
00:09:25,069 --> 00:09:25,987
Yeah, I see that.

201
00:09:26,070 --> 00:09:27,905
Derek, what are you doing here?

202
00:09:27,989 --> 00:09:29,449
You're supposed to stay at Mindy's.

203
00:09:29,532 --> 00:09:32,827
I can't help it.
I'm just such a proud daddy Derek.

204
00:09:32,910 --> 00:09:36,331
I mean, will you look at all these
beautiful babies that we made?

205
00:09:36,414 --> 00:09:39,751
She made them, dude.
You barely did anything.

206
00:09:39,834 --> 00:09:42,170
Probably just made all the butts.

207
00:09:42,253 --> 00:09:43,296
I did make all the butts.

208
00:09:43,379 --> 00:09:45,214
- I made that butt, I made that butt.
- Mmm, right.

209
00:09:45,298 --> 00:09:47,175
I made both those butts.

210
00:09:47,258 --> 00:09:49,302
Derek, you have to stay at Mindy's house.

211
00:09:49,385 --> 00:09:51,012
What if one of our new humans sees you

212
00:09:51,095 --> 00:09:53,681
and starts asking questions
about the weirdo in the tux?

213
00:09:53,765 --> 00:09:57,060
Say no more. But before I leave,
can I have a hug

214
00:09:57,143 --> 00:09:59,937
in celebration of everything
that we created?

215
00:10:00,021 --> 00:10:01,814
- Okay.
- Aww!

216
00:10:01,898 --> 00:10:04,025
That feels so...

217
00:10:05,151 --> 00:10:06,235
Derek.

218
00:10:07,570 --> 00:10:10,907
You are all, simply put, good people.

219
00:10:10,990 --> 00:10:13,660
The point of the video
is to make them all confront

220
00:10:13,743 --> 00:10:15,828
what kind of people they were on Earth.

221
00:10:15,912 --> 00:10:21,167
Keep a close eye on our four subjects.
Try to gauge their reactions.

222
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:24,629
The subtlest glances,
the tiniest flinches...

223
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,757
What about shaking someone by the head?

224
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,425
What does that mean?

225
00:10:29,509 --> 00:10:30,718
Oh, boy.

226
00:10:31,594 --> 00:10:35,056
Hey, Simone. Everything okay?

227
00:10:35,139 --> 00:10:36,724
Yeah. Well, no.

228
00:10:36,808 --> 00:10:40,061
Well, actually, it doesn't matter.
None of this is real.

229
00:10:40,812 --> 00:10:42,563
- Sorry?
- I'm a neuroscientist,

230
00:10:42,647 --> 00:10:44,107
so I get what's going on here.

231
00:10:44,190 --> 00:10:47,026
You know, clearly, I was in
some kind of horrible accident,

232
00:10:47,110 --> 00:10:49,654
I'm on my deathbed, and this entire thing
is just a hallucination

233
00:10:49,737 --> 00:10:52,281
constructed by my damaged brain
as it slowly shuts down.

234
00:10:52,365 --> 00:10:53,282
It's not real.

235
00:10:53,366 --> 00:10:57,495
So, I'm just gonna wander around
until I wake up or die.

236
00:10:57,578 --> 00:10:59,747
See ya later, figments of my imagination.

237
00:11:02,667 --> 00:11:07,088
She's just gonna go get some popcorn
from the... river.

238
00:11:07,672 --> 00:11:10,258
There's a popcorn river.
I'll show you guys later.

239
00:11:10,341 --> 00:11:12,927
Uh, she said keep going without her,
so let's roll it.

240
00:11:13,010 --> 00:11:14,804
Janet, make a popcorn river.

241
00:11:14,887 --> 00:11:17,348
Everyone else,
meet at Mindy's in ten minutes.

242
00:11:17,932 --> 00:11:21,269
Well... we're off to a fantastic start.

243
00:11:21,352 --> 00:11:24,147
I wish I could stay and help,
but this system is so complex

244
00:11:24,230 --> 00:11:27,358
that if I lose concentration
for even one billionth of a second,

245
00:11:27,442 --> 00:11:30,111
the entire neighborhood could collapse
in on itself like a dying star.

246
00:11:31,404 --> 00:11:33,739
Also, Brent wants a BLT.

247
00:11:33,823 --> 00:11:35,992
Simone's reaction is fairly common.

248
00:11:36,075 --> 00:11:37,785
When I worked in the Bad Place,

249
00:11:37,869 --> 00:11:40,496
some people just wouldn't believe it
when they heard they were dead.

250
00:11:40,580 --> 00:11:41,622
How did you convince them?

251
00:11:41,706 --> 00:11:45,126
They'd usually come around
by the third or fourth day of mouth fleas.

252
00:11:45,209 --> 00:11:47,128
Obviously, not an option here.

253
00:11:47,211 --> 00:11:49,213
But if Simone doesn't think this is real,

254
00:11:49,297 --> 00:11:51,340
she definitely won't become
a better person.

255
00:11:51,424 --> 00:11:54,051
Who can convince her
that this actually is the afterlife?

256
00:11:54,135 --> 00:11:56,929
We need someone authoritative
and reassuring

257
00:11:57,013 --> 00:11:59,640
like Nelson Mandela
or Sir Patrick Stewart,

258
00:11:59,724 --> 00:12:02,477
or, really, any of my old
racquetball partners would do.

259
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:03,769
Oh, I know who it should be.

260
00:12:03,853 --> 00:12:06,105
If you say Blake Bortles,
I'm gonna slap you a lot.

261
00:12:06,189 --> 00:12:08,483
Chidi. I believe everything
Chidi ever tells me

262
00:12:08,566 --> 00:12:10,318
because of his brain and how he looks like

263
00:12:10,401 --> 00:12:12,695
one of those owls
that graduated from college.

264
00:12:12,778 --> 00:12:14,071
Of course!

265
00:12:14,155 --> 00:12:18,367
Time to activate our ethical sleeper agent
and introduce him to Simone.

266
00:12:18,451 --> 00:12:19,577
Uh, I don't know.

267
00:12:19,660 --> 00:12:21,579
Simone isn't struggling
with a philosophy problem.

268
00:12:21,662 --> 00:12:24,707
She's just, you know, like... being silly.

269
00:12:24,790 --> 00:12:27,793
Let's just get her to the welcome party
and I'm sure she'll be fine.

270
00:12:27,877 --> 00:12:31,088
Eleanor, look what my brain did!

271
00:12:32,131 --> 00:12:34,008
It's not real, and neither are you.

272
00:12:34,091 --> 00:12:37,345
I'm in a coma and none of this is real

273
00:12:37,428 --> 00:12:40,723
Okay, I know this is bad
and we need a new approach,

274
00:12:41,474 --> 00:12:43,726
but she is wearing
the hell out of those foam fingers.

275
00:12:47,188 --> 00:12:48,147
Root-a-toot-toot

276
00:12:48,231 --> 00:12:50,858
Dude, Janet told you to stay at Mindy's.

277
00:12:50,942 --> 00:12:56,322
I know. I just came to mix myself
a Derek and then I'll be on my way.

278
00:12:57,114 --> 00:13:00,284
Before you leave, I wanna call a truce.

279
00:13:00,368 --> 00:13:01,536
All right.

280
00:13:01,619 --> 00:13:04,956
I feel like you're trying
to get under my skin, but it's okay.

281
00:13:05,039 --> 00:13:07,291
I've decided to rise above it.

282
00:13:07,375 --> 00:13:09,210
Well spoken, Mr. Mendoza.

283
00:13:09,293 --> 00:13:11,754
Let me say in response...

284
00:13:12,421 --> 00:13:16,050
I will destroy you.

285
00:13:16,634 --> 00:13:22,723
Janet is and always will be
my mommy-girlfriend.

286
00:13:22,807 --> 00:13:26,185
You have crossed the Rubicon now, pal.

287
00:13:29,855 --> 00:13:31,274
Mmm...

288
00:13:31,983 --> 00:13:33,150
Okay, status report.

289
00:13:33,234 --> 00:13:34,860
What have we learned about Linda?

290
00:13:34,944 --> 00:13:35,903
Little, I'm afraid.

291
00:13:35,987 --> 00:13:39,282
I tried talking to her, but it was
the dullest conversation I have ever had.

292
00:13:39,365 --> 00:13:42,785
And this is coming from someone who
once split a Xanax with Peter Sarsgaard.

293
00:13:42,868 --> 00:13:45,496
Frankly, I'm glad she's boring.
We have enough to worry about.

294
00:13:45,580 --> 00:13:48,499
- How is Brent doing?
- About the same, I'd say.

295
00:13:48,583 --> 00:13:49,417
Princeton.

296
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:52,003
Graduated in the top half
of the bottom half of my class.

297
00:13:52,086 --> 00:13:54,839
Rowing team, sailing team,
class president,

298
00:13:54,922 --> 00:13:56,007
I hung out with all those guys.

299
00:13:56,090 --> 00:13:59,135
Okay. And John,
our favorite gossip columnist?

300
00:13:59,218 --> 00:14:02,597
Luckily, before I died, I pumped my face
with six vials of Juvederm.

301
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:05,433
I'm hoping that my corpse
looks like a waxed tile floor.

302
00:14:05,516 --> 00:14:08,144
My ex-boyf is gonna be supes jeal'.

303
00:14:08,227 --> 00:14:11,022
