trying to see who gets me.

304
00:14:11,105 --> 00:14:13,816
Our biggest liability right now is Simone.

305
00:14:13,899 --> 00:14:17,278
Let's try to keep the three of them
away from her.

306
00:14:18,654 --> 00:14:22,325
We can't wait any longer.
We have to introduce Simone to Chidi.

307
00:14:22,408 --> 00:14:24,994
Why? I think she's doing great.

308
00:14:26,704 --> 00:14:27,705
See?

309
00:14:27,788 --> 00:14:29,665
She's getting all the cake-pushing
out of her system.

310
00:14:29,749 --> 00:14:34,211
I know it's painful to think
of the two of them... connecting.

311
00:14:34,295 --> 00:14:37,173
But Chidi made an incredible sacrifice.

312
00:14:37,256 --> 00:14:40,801
He had his memories erased
so he could help people.

313
00:14:40,885 --> 00:14:44,055
And if we don't let him help Simone,
it'll be all for nothing.

314
00:14:45,056 --> 00:14:46,223
Fine.

315
00:14:47,642 --> 00:14:50,686
Stupid ethical, reasonable argument.

316
00:14:50,770 --> 00:14:53,105
Wish you were a cake. Push you over.

317
00:14:53,189 --> 00:14:56,567
- Are you still muttering?
- No, I stopped.

318
00:14:57,276 --> 00:14:59,987
Stupid, good-hearing, reformed demon.

319
00:15:01,739 --> 00:15:02,573
Whoa!

320
00:15:05,534 --> 00:15:07,328
Hey, there, Simone!

321
00:15:07,411 --> 00:15:09,622
- Shoving people in the pool, huh?
- Yeah.

322
00:15:09,705 --> 00:15:12,667
Just testing the laws of physics
here in my nonsense brain-jail.

323
00:15:12,750 --> 00:15:16,671
- Who's this?
- This is Chidi Anagonye.

324
00:15:16,754 --> 00:15:19,507
He was a professor
of ethics and moral philosophy,

325
00:15:19,590 --> 00:15:21,050
so I figured he might be able to help.

326
00:15:21,133 --> 00:15:25,054
Chidi Anagonye. That sounds so familiar.
Where did you teach?

327
00:15:25,137 --> 00:15:27,390
St. John's University in Sydney.

328
00:15:27,473 --> 00:15:29,433
Of course. I used to teach there.

329
00:15:29,517 --> 00:15:31,394
I must have seen his name
on the faculty list

330
00:15:31,477 --> 00:15:34,897
and now my dying brain
is just leaking out random information.

331
00:15:35,940 --> 00:15:38,359
The human mind is truly incredible.

332
00:15:39,193 --> 00:15:41,946
I want something else

333
00:15:42,029 --> 00:15:44,156
To get me through this

334
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:46,742
Semi-charmed kind of life, baby, baby

335
00:15:46,826 --> 00:15:49,203
Sorry... uh, what's happening now?

336
00:15:49,286 --> 00:15:51,414
When I was a kid, my CD alarm clock broke

337
00:15:51,497 --> 00:15:53,249
and it used to wake me up
to that song every day,

338
00:15:53,332 --> 00:15:56,002
so now I'm singing it
to try and wake myself up.

339
00:15:56,085 --> 00:15:57,878
Okay. Well, it was nice meeting you.

340
00:15:57,962 --> 00:16:02,091
Nice to meet you, too, cute guy generated
by my rapidly-decaying temporal lobe.

341
00:16:07,638 --> 00:16:08,472
- Hey...
- You know,

342
00:16:08,556 --> 00:16:11,642
it's bad enough that you guys
have taken over my house for a year

343
00:16:11,726 --> 00:16:13,561
and I've had to move into the attic,

344
00:16:13,644 --> 00:16:15,229
but now I have to walk in to find

345
00:16:15,312 --> 00:16:17,982
Darth Vader's turd
in the middle of my living room.

346
00:16:18,065 --> 00:16:19,316
I mean, what is this?

347
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:20,818
No time to explain.

348
00:16:21,402 --> 00:16:22,737
Also, I kinda forgot.

349
00:16:22,820 --> 00:16:24,530
Where is Derek's plunger?
The one that kills him?

350
00:16:25,656 --> 00:16:28,367
Yeah, I used to do this
whenever I needed some alone time.

351
00:16:28,451 --> 00:16:32,079
Once, I rebooted him
just because he was breathing super loud.

352
00:16:32,163 --> 00:16:35,082
Then, when he woke up,
he was like, "I don't breathe."

353
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:36,459
So I don't know what I heard.

354
00:16:36,542 --> 00:16:39,045
Well, I'm doing this because
he's trying to steal my girlfriend.

355
00:16:39,128 --> 00:16:41,130
Yeah. You don't need to justify it.

356
00:16:41,213 --> 00:16:43,215
Again, I do it all the time.

357
00:16:44,091 --> 00:16:46,218
No! Mindy, please wait. Don't kill me.

358
00:16:46,302 --> 00:16:47,136
Oh!

359
00:16:47,887 --> 00:16:50,056
It's you? Okay.

360
00:16:50,139 --> 00:16:51,974
Well, you certainly
don't have the Dereks to...

361
00:17:02,860 --> 00:17:03,986
Yeah!

362
00:17:04,695 --> 00:17:05,529
Oh!

363
00:17:05,613 --> 00:17:06,739
It's always good.

364
00:17:07,907 --> 00:17:09,825
You know what, Simone?
Think of it this way.

365
00:17:09,909 --> 00:17:13,746
If this is really all a hallucination,
doesn't it seem kinda basic?

366
00:17:13,829 --> 00:17:16,624
I mean, surely your brain
would imagine something weirder

367
00:17:16,707 --> 00:17:18,501
than just a nice cocktail party.

368
00:17:18,584 --> 00:17:19,794
You mean like that?

369
00:17:19,877 --> 00:17:22,421
Attention, I have been Derek'd.

370
00:17:22,505 --> 00:17:25,633
That's probably my doctor.
This is all in my head.

371
00:17:25,716 --> 00:17:26,967
I'm gonna go eat a knife.

372
00:17:27,051 --> 00:17:29,637
Attention. Murder has been me.

373
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:31,138
Let me get this straight.

374
00:17:31,222 --> 00:17:33,891
Derek "made mean eyes at you,"

375
00:17:33,974 --> 00:17:36,727
so you went to Mindy's house
and murdered him?

376
00:17:36,811 --> 00:17:39,021
Yeah, dawg, but his eyes were really mean.

377
00:17:39,105 --> 00:17:40,856
You're probably thinking this...

378
00:17:42,650 --> 00:17:44,068
but they were more like this...

379
00:17:45,444 --> 00:17:47,238
Jason, why did you kill Derek?

380
00:17:47,321 --> 00:17:50,574
I had to get his giant head out of the sky
before any of the humans could see,

381
00:17:50,658 --> 00:17:51,617
and it was not easy.

382
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:54,203
I was scared Derek was trying
to slide into your DMs.

383
00:17:54,286 --> 00:17:55,913
I hate being scared. It's scary.

384
00:17:55,996 --> 00:17:56,956
I don't have time for this.

385
00:17:57,039 --> 00:17:58,916
I am running a neighborhood
and its residents,

386
00:17:58,999 --> 00:18:02,086
and Eleanor just casually orders me
to make popcorn rivers

387
00:18:02,169 --> 00:18:05,381
and Brent won't stop calling me for stuff.

388
00:18:05,464 --> 00:18:06,799
Ugh!

389
00:18:06,882 --> 00:18:08,592
Are we still boyfriend/not-a-girlfriend?

390
00:18:08,676 --> 00:18:10,052
We'll talk about it later.

391
00:18:10,136 --> 00:18:12,680
Okay. Executive decision.
Forget about Simone.

392
00:18:12,763 --> 00:18:15,641
Janet, make sure she doesn't come
in contact with the other humans.

393
00:18:15,724 --> 00:18:16,684
Let's focus on Linda.

394
00:18:16,767 --> 00:18:19,770
We ought to be able to figure her out.
We can just liven her up a bit.

395
00:18:19,854 --> 00:18:22,731
We'll just sprinkle some cocaine
on her peppermints or something.

396
00:18:22,815 --> 00:18:25,025
Does anyone else find it suspicious

397
00:18:25,109 --> 00:18:28,070
that the Bad Place
sent someone so... dull?

398
00:18:28,154 --> 00:18:29,780
No, it makes perfect sense to me.

399
00:18:29,864 --> 00:18:31,782
They are trying to drive us insane

400
00:18:31,866 --> 00:18:34,702
by giving us
a big, boring glob of plain yogurt.

401
00:18:34,785 --> 00:18:37,371
Tomorrow morning,
we start Operation Linda.

402
00:18:37,454 --> 00:18:39,165
Okay, you heard the lady.

403
00:18:39,248 --> 00:18:41,333
We'll meet in the town square
bright and early.

404
00:18:41,417 --> 00:18:42,585
Janet, set up for Flying Day.

405
00:18:43,210 --> 00:18:44,086
Cool.

406
00:18:44,170 --> 00:18:46,255
I'm not busy or anything,
so that'll be easy.

407
00:18:47,339 --> 00:18:48,257
Off you go!

408
00:18:48,799 --> 00:18:51,177
Whoo-hoo!

409
00:18:51,802 --> 00:18:55,014
Linda. How are you
enjoying the Good Place?

410
00:18:55,097 --> 00:18:56,265
It's good.

411
00:18:57,850 --> 00:18:59,185
Everyone's flying.

412
00:18:59,268 --> 00:19:01,312
You don't want to go flying any higher?

413
00:19:01,395 --> 00:19:02,563
No, thanks.

414
00:19:03,522 --> 00:19:04,523
Well, okay.

415
00:19:04,607 --> 00:19:06,650
It says in your file
that you liked knitting.

416
00:19:06,734 --> 00:19:08,777
Would you like to do
some knitting right now?

417
00:19:08,861 --> 00:19:09,904
No, thanks.

418
00:19:09,987 --> 00:19:12,531
Is there another activity
you'd like to do now?

419
00:19:13,157 --> 00:19:16,452
You also enjoyed... listening to birds?

420
00:19:17,077 --> 00:19:18,204
Man, Linda.

421
00:19:18,829 --> 00:19:20,206
You don't even look at them?

422
00:19:20,831 --> 00:19:23,417
Let's go hear some birds. What do you say?

423
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:25,169
I'm gonna go get another peppermint.

424
00:19:25,252 --> 00:19:26,462
- No...
- Come on, Linds.

425
00:19:26,545 --> 00:19:29,548
You can have literally anything
that you could poss...

426
00:19:30,466 --> 00:19:31,383
What the...

427
00:19:42,228 --> 00:19:44,271
Okay. So...

428
00:19:44,355 --> 00:19:46,607
Maybe she's less boring than I thought.

429
00:19:49,818 --> 00:19:51,445
So, let me get this straight, Shawn.

430
00:19:51,528 --> 00:19:55,282
You sent a demon in disguise
as one of the subjects?

431
00:19:55,366 --> 00:19:57,368
Yes, he did, Your Honor.

432
00:20:03,082 --> 00:20:06,043
Luckily, none of the other test subjects
saw the mess he made.

433
00:20:06,126 --> 00:20:10,256
But he put the experiment at risk
and he attacked me and Eleanor.

434
00:20:10,339 --> 00:20:12,508
And, I'm sorry, where's your shirt?

435
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:14,760
I think it got stuck in the skin suit.

436
00:20:14,843 --> 00:20:16,303
Well, keep it there.

437
00:20:16,387 --> 00:20:19,139
Damn it, Chris. You were supposed
to slowly undermine them

438
00:20:19,223 --> 00:20:21,392
and gradually sabotage the experiment,

439
00:20:21,475 --> 00:20:23,686
not just go ham on day two,
you fart plume.

440
00:20:23,769 --> 00:20:25,646
I told you, I'm not an actor.

441
00:20:25,729 --> 00:20:27,690
And when you get back here,
you won't be anything.

442
00:20:27,773 --> 00:20:30,776
Okay, fine, yes, busted. I'm a rascal.

443
00:20:30,859 --> 00:20:33,070
We'll come pick him up
and replace him with an actual human.

444
00:20:33,153 --> 00:20:36,240
You will do nothing of the sort, mon ami.

445
00:20:36,323 --> 00:20:38,617
This outrageous act must be punished.

446
00:20:39,201 --> 00:20:41,787
Chidi will be the fourth subject
in this experiment.

447
00:20:41,870 --> 00:20:43,330
No, no, no, no, no.

448
00:20:43,414 --> 00:20:45,582
He's perfect because he's already
had his memories erased.

449
00:20:45,666 --> 00:20:48,627
Although you can't erase that booty.
Know what I'm sayin', blondie?

450
00:20:48,711 --> 00:20:51,130
All due respect, Your Honor,
keep it in your robe.

451
00:20:51,213 --> 00:20:54,425
What she means is,
"Thank you, Your Honor, we accept."

452
00:20:54,508 --> 00:20:56,010
Chidi's gonna be our fourth subject.

453
00:20:56,093 --> 00:20:57,845
Chidi can't be part of the experiment.

454
00:20:57,928 --> 00:20:59,221
They already know that he can improve.

455
00:20:59,305 --> 00:21:02,099
That's like studying for a test
then acing the test.

456
00:21:02,182 --> 00:21:04,268
- It's cheating.
- How is that cheating?

457
00:21:04,351 --> 00:21:07,354
You're just falsely accusing us
of what you actually did.

458
00:21:07,438 --> 00:21:08,647
No, that's what you're doing.

459
00:21:08,731 --> 00:21:10,441
Shawn, I don't have time for this.

460
00:21:10,524 --> 00:21:12,735
I just started Deadwood, finally,

461
00:21:12,818 --> 00:21:15,988
and I need my daily dose
of Timothy Olyphant,

462
00:21:16,071 --> 00:21:17,656
so I'm gonna make this short.

463
00:21:17,740 --> 00:21:21,910
If you so much as breathe
on this experiment again,

464
00:21:21,994 --> 00:21:25,456
I will restart the entire thing
from scratch,

465
00:21:25,539 --> 00:21:29,209
and then I will personally
rip off your eyelids

466
00:21:29,293 --> 00:21:34,089
and make you watch heartwarming videos
of soldiers coming home to their dogs.

467
00:21:35,424 --> 00:21:37,051
Whoa! Slow down.

468
00:21:41,013 --> 00:21:43,390
Did you put those trash cans
there just so you could crash into them?

469
00:21:43,474 --> 00:21:45,976
That wasn't my fault. I was texting.

470
00:21:46,060 --> 00:21:47,436
Okay, let him go, dung buckets.

471
00:21:47,519 --> 00:21:48,896
Nice try.

472
00:21:48,979 --> 00:21:51,857
We'll put him on the train
and handcuff him to a bench.

473
00:21:51,940 --> 00:21:53,025
Come on.

474
00:21:53,108 --> 00:21:56,111
Yeah, forgive us if we don't trust you
not to cheat again.

475
00:21:56,904 --> 00:21:58,697
Surprised you figured out
that Linda was a fake,

476
00:21:58,781 --> 00:22:01,700
because we all thought
you were too stupid.

477
00:22:01,784 --> 00:22:04,536
Well, it was actually Tahani
who got suspicious.

478
00:22:04,620 --> 00:22:06,246
Oh!

479
00:22:06,330 --> 00:22:08,123
That is so embarrassing for you.

480
00:22:08,207 --> 00:22:11,585
Seems like you're royally forking this up
just like we knew you would.

481
00:22:11,668 --> 00:22:13,170
Okay.

482
00:22:13,253 --> 00:22:14,254
Take off.

483
00:22:14,338 --> 00:22:15,881
And give Shawn a message for me.

484
00:22:15,964 --> 00:22:18,258
Tell him that we said, "Booyah!"

485
00:22:19,426 --> 00:22:21,970
Make sure you do the hand motion,
like, "Booyah!"

486
00:22:22,054 --> 00:22:23,806
- Are you listening to me?
- Okay, Michael...

487
00:22:23,889 --> 00:22:25,265
- No, show me how you're gonna do it.
- That's fine.

488
00:22:25,349 --> 00:22:27,810
No, it's important
that she does the hand thing

489
00:22:27,893 --> 00:22:29,770
because it really drives the point home.

